				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>size</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px">
<mono>f++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
size(param)
</pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center">
<mono>n++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
\@size(param)
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>size</mono> function takes a single parameter and returns its length/size. 
				</p>

				<h4 id="f++-eg">
					f++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>size</mono> being used with <mono>f++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums lang-nift">
:=(string, str="hello, world!")
console(size(str))</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>size</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums lang-nift">
\@:=(string, str="hello, world!")
\@console(\@size(str))</pre>
</div>
				</p>
